  <h2>The Power of RLAs</h2>
  <p>Now that we’ve seen how each type of audit is conducted, it’s time to put them to the test. Here is where we’ll see the real power of risk-limiting audits. You’ll have three sliders at your disposal: the ability to determine the total number of votes cast, the margin of victory, and the percentage of votes to check for the traditional type of audit. Play around with the sliders. Do you notice anything interesting?</p>

